        <bioghist id="ref12">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Thomas Jefferson served as president of the United States, 1801-1809, and of the American Philosophical Society, 1797-1815. John Sibley was an Indian agent for Orleans Territory, 1805-1814, and gathered vocabularies of tribes within the territory and reported his findings to Jefferson.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <acqinfo id="ref9">
            <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition note</head>
            <p>Presented by Thomas Jefferson and accessioned, 1817 (1817 51356).</p>
            <p></p>
        </acqinfo>
        <altformavail id="ref5">
